 story of fragility, complexity, living “on the edge,” and the (re)-building of identity.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aHomeless youthzCanadavCase studies. 0aHomeless youthzCanada. 0aHomeless youth-Canada-Case studies. 0aHomeless youth-Canada. 4aSocial Science: Social Work. 4aSocial Science: Sociology. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Poverty & Homelessness.2bisacsh  aCanada homelessness.  aarts-based research.  acomic book narratives.  ahomeless youth.  ahousing stability.  aknowledge translation.  alongitudinal research.  apathways off of street.  aresearch ethics.  astreet exiting.  astreet youth.  ayouth in transition.  ayouth marginalization.  ayouth poverty.1 aFrederick, Tyler, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aKidd, Sean, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package 2018z978311127363108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2018z978311127598740uhttps://doi.org/10.51644/978177112334140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781771123341423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781771123341/original  a978-3-11-127363-1  ACUP Complete eBook-Package 2018b2018  a978-3-11-127598-7  ACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2018b2018  aGBV-deGruyter-alles